    <main class="container">
        <div class="content-container">
            <h1>DMCA Policy</h1>
            
            <div class="last-updated">
                <div><strong>Effective Date:</strong> January 17, 2026</div>
                <div><strong>Last Updated:</strong> January 17, 2026</div>
            </div>

            <div class="important-box">
                <p><strong>⚠️ IMPORTANT LEGAL NOTICE:</strong> This DMCA Policy outlines our procedures for handling copyright infringement claims. We respect intellectual property rights and comply with the Digital Millennium Copyright Act (DMCA).</p>
            </div>

            <h2>1. DMCA Compliance Statement</h2>
            <p>Shorts Creator Toolkit ("we," "our," or "us") respects the intellectual property rights of others and expects our users to do the same. We comply with the Digital Millennium Copyright Act (DMCA) and other applicable copyright laws.</p>
            
            <div class="legal-box">
                <h3><i class="fas fa-balance-scale"></i> Our Position on Copyright</h3>
                <p>We provide tools for content creators that operate within the boundaries of fair use and copyright law. Our tools do not host or store copyrighted content. We act as an intermediary service provider as defined under the DMCA.</p>
            </div>

            <h2>2. Reporting Copyright Infringement</h2>
            <p>If you believe that your copyrighted work has been copied in a way that constitutes copyright infringement and is accessible through our Service, please notify our Copyright Agent as specified below.</p>

            <h3><i class="fas fa-exclamation-circle"></i> Required Information for DMCA Notice</h3>
            <p>A proper DMCA notice must include the following information:</p>
            
            <div class="dmca-format">
                <div class="dmca-item">
                    <span class="dmca-label">1. Identification of Copyrighted Work</span>
                    <p>A description of the copyrighted work that you claim has been infringed, including the URL or other specific location where the material you claim is infringing is located.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="dmca-item">
                    <span class="dmca-label">2. Your Contact Information</span>
                    <p>Your full name, mailing address, telephone number, and email address where we can contact you.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="dmca-item">
                    <span class="dmca-label">3. Statement of Good Faith Belief</span>
                    <p>A statement that you have a good faith belief that the disputed use is not authorized by the copyright owner, its agent, or the law.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="dmca-item">
                    <span class="dmca-label">4. Statement Under Penalty of Perjury</span>
                    <p>A statement, made under penalty of perjury, that the above information in your notice is accurate and that you are the copyright owner or authorized to act on the copyright owner's behalf.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="dmca-item">
                    <span class="dmca-label">5. Electronic Signature</span>
                    <p>Your electronic or physical signature as the copyright owner or authorized representative.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h2>3. DMCA Notice Submission</h2>
            <div class="contact-info">
                <h3><i class="fas fa-envelope"></i> Submit DMCA Notice To:</h3>
                <p><strong>Copyright Agent:</strong> DMCA Compliance Officer</p>
                <p><strong>Email:</strong> dmca@shortscreator.tools</p>
                <p><strong>Response Time:</strong> We aim to respond to all DMCA notices within 48 business hours</p>
            </div>

            <div class="process-box">
                <h3><i class="fas fa-cogs"></i> Our DMCA Process</h3>
                <p>Upon receipt of a valid DMCA notice, we will:</p>
                <ol>
                    <li>Acknowledge receipt of your notice within 48 business hours</li>
                    <li>Promptly investigate the alleged infringement</li>
                    <li>Remove or disable access to the allegedly infringing material</li>
                    <li>Notify the user who posted the material of the takedown</li>
                    <li>Provide the user with information about submitting a counter-notice</li>
                </ol>
            </div>

            <h2>4. Counter-Notification Process</h2>
            <p>If you believe that material you posted was removed or access to it was disabled by mistake or misidentification, you may submit a counter-notification.</p>

            <div class="counter-notice">
                <h3><i class="fas fa-undo-alt"></i> Counter-Notice Requirements</h3>
                <p>A valid counter-notice must include:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Your physical or electronic signature</li>
                    <li>Identification of the material that has been removed</li>
                    <li>A statement under penalty of perjury that you have a good faith belief the material was removed by mistake</li>
                    <li>Your name, address, and telephone number</li>
                    <li>A statement consenting to jurisdiction in the federal court where you reside</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h2>5. Repeat Infringer Policy</h2>
            <p>In accordance with the DMCA and other applicable laws, we have adopted a policy of terminating, in appropriate circumstances, users who are deemed to be repeat infringers. We may also, at our sole discretion, limit access to the Service and/or terminate the accounts of any users who infringe any intellectual property rights of others.</p>

            <h2>6. False Claims Warning</h2>
            <div class="important-box">
                <p><strong>⚠️ WARNING:</strong> Making false claims of copyright infringement is illegal and may result in liability for damages under Section 512(f) of the DMCA. This includes court costs and attorney's fees.</p>
            </div>

            <h2>7. Copyright Agent Information</h2>
            <div class="contact-info">
                <h3><i class="fas fa-user-tie"></i> Designated Copyright Agent</h3>
                <p><strong>Name:</strong> DMCA Compliance Officer</p>
                <p><strong>Service:</strong> Shorts Creator Toolkit</p>
                <p><strong>Email:</strong> dmca@shortscreator.tools</p>
                <p><strong>Processing Time:</strong> 48 business hours for initial response</p>
            </div>

            <h2>8. Third-Party Content Disclaimer</h2>
            <p>Our Service provides tools that may access or reference third-party content (YouTube videos, Instagram reels, etc.). We are not responsible for the content on these third-party platforms. Any copyright infringement claims regarding third-party content should be directed to the respective platform.</p>

            <h2>9. Fair Use Considerations</h2>
            <p>Our tools are designed to operate within the boundaries of fair use as defined by copyright law. Fair use includes purposes such as criticism, comment, news reporting, teaching, scholarship, and research. If you believe your content qualifies as fair use, please mention this in your correspondence.</p>

            <h2>10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
            <p>We reserve the right to modify this DMCA Policy at any time. We will notify users of any changes by posting the new policy on this page and updating the "Last Updated" date. Your continued use of the Service after any changes constitutes your acceptance of the new policy.</p>

            <div class="legal-box">
                <h3><i class="fas fa-gavel"></i> Legal Disclaimer</h3>
                <p>This DMCA Policy is provided for informational purposes only and does not constitute legal advice. If you need legal advice regarding copyright infringement, please consult with a qualified attorney.</p>
            </div>

            <h2>11. Return to Free Tools</h2>
            <p>Ready to create amazing Shorts? Return to our free tools:</p>
